.*X*                                                            
FYI, this HELP file has been specially prepared to run through TUNA.X (LEN=79)
prior to running through HERMAN.  This action will guarantee that the lines of
text in it will fill a screen as much as possible, and that more lines will end
up per screen.
.*R*
.*A*
:PFS.X is an LADC-specific TEXT macro used to generate Product Function
Specifications, Engineering Function Specifications, Master Project Plans.
.*B*
Usage:   (this file should be copied into :LIBRARY on your system)
 
 
  ***************************************************************
  ***************    Following is an example of the setup
  ***************    required for this macro.  Specify:
  ***************      "M" for Master Project Plan,
  ***************      "P" for Product Function Specification,
  ***************      "E" for Engineering Function Specification
  ***************    on the ..:PFS macro call line.
  ***************************************************************
  ********** .SRV TITLE "CP-6 X00 RELEASE MASTER PROJECT PLAN"
  ********** .SRV IDENTIFIER "####"
  ********** .SRV RELEASE "Revision C"
  ********** .SRV LOCATION "Los Angeles, California"
  ********** .SRV DIST_CODE "####"
  ********** .SRV DIVISION "Software Development Operations"
  ********** .SRV ORGANIZATION "Los Angeles Development Center"
  ********** .SRV AUTHOR "A. Manager"
  ********** .SRV APPROVAL_DATE "October 31, 1986"
  ********** .SRV RELEASE_DATE "September 30, 1986"
  ********** ..:PFS "M"   (or "P" or "E")
  ***************************************************************
.*K* XINDEX
:PFS.X
.*R*
AID=OFFICE_AUTOMATION
.*R*
AID=DOCUMENTATION
.*R*
TEXT_MACRO
.*K* XINDEX_ABSTRACT
TOOL=:PFS
.*R*
An LADC-specific TEXT macro which generates the correct title page and
format for Product Function Specifications (PFS), Engineering Function
Specifications (EFS), or Master Project Plans (MPP).
